8 An Act relating to medical marijuana; requiring the
display of certain signage in dispensaries and
9 businesses; providing contents and requirements of
sign; requiring owners pay cost of signs; providing
10 for codification; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 427.30 of Title 63, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. Every medical marijuana dispensary or any place medical
19 marijuana or tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) products are sold shall post
20 and display at all times a printed sign, with a minimum height of
21 eight and one-half (8 1/2) inches and a minimum width of eleven (11)
22 inches with a font size of no less than 48 points for the text, near
23 the cash register or place of checkout and at least two other highly
24 visible places in the store, which shall read as follows:
Req. No. 13180 Page 1

1 WARNING: INGESTING THC PRODUCTS WHILE PREGNANT IS NOT HEALTHY
2 FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF AN UNBORN CHILD.
3 B. The signage shall be produced at the expense of the owner of
4 the business establishment.
5 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
